Wash and dry all produce. Core and seed @Poblano Peppers{2}, then cut into ¼-inch-wide
strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Heat a large drizzle of
@Vegetable Oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add poblanos and onion
and cook, tossing occasionally, until softened and slightly charred, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice @Radishes{6}. Thinly slice @Jalapeño{1} into rounds, removing
ribs and seeds for less heat. Quarter @Lime{2}.

Combine @Sour Cream{8%tbsp}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp} (we'll use more in the next
step), and a squeeze of lime in a #small bowl{}, then stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time
until thinned to a drizzly consistency. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}, and more
lime (to taste).

Once poblanos and onion have softened, toss in @Ground Turkey{20%oz}, @Mexican Spice
Blend{1%tbsp}, and another @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp} to same pan (you'll have
some Southwest spice left over). Break up turkey into pieces. Cook, tossing
occasionally, until no longer pink, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> If your pan is too small to fit both the meat and the veggies, remove the veggies
> and set aside while cooking the turkey.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{12} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high until warm,
about ~{30%seconds}.

> Alternatively, wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven for 5 minutes at 425 degrees.

Fill each tortilla with turkey and veggies, radishes, and jalapeño (to taste). Sprinkle
with @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}. Drizzle with crema. Tear @Cilantro{1/2%oz} leaves from
stems and scatter over. Serve with lime quarters on the side for squeezing over.